e of Western fiction, crime fiction and its place in the Japanese popular imagination were forever changed by Kidô’s "unsung Sherlock Holmes." These stories—still widely read today—are crucial to our understanding of modern Japan and its aspirations toward a literature that steps outside the shadow of the West to stand on its own.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jan 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aJAPANESE LIT PUB & PROMO CTR1 aMacDonald, Ian08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHawaii eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486466840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824864668423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824864668.jpg  a978-3-11-056414-3  Hawaii eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066325-9  UHP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK